 //   EF Core 8 stored the Cosmos `id` as "Product|123" (via a shadow
 //   property named "__id").  EF Core 9 maps the CLR key directly to `id`,
 //   producing just "123".  Existing 500K documents still have "Product|123"
 //   and will NOT be found by EF Core 9 unless we preserve the old format.
 //   FIX: We introduce an explicit `CosmosId` property that carries the
 //   legacy format, mark it as the Cosmos identity, and keep the integer
 //   `Id` as a separate stored property.
 //
 // BREAKING CHANGE 3 – Synchronous I/O throws at runtime
 //   The Cosmos provider now throws InvalidOperationException for sync calls
 //   like ToList(), First(), SaveChanges(), etc.
 //   FIX: Use async equivalents (ToListAsync, SaveChangesAsync, …).
 //
 // BREAKING CHANGE 4 – HasIndex is not supported on Cosmos
 //   In EF 8 this was silently ignored.  EF 9 may warn or throw during
 //   model validation.  Cosmos indexes must be managed through the Azure
 //   portal, ARM/Bicep templates, or the Cosmos SDK – not EF Core.
 //   FIX: Remove the HasIndex call.
 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

